<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Intro</div>

<div class=itemtext>X3 was one of the greatest MM games ever.  Besides some great music, most notbly Gravity Beetle's theme, this game has TONS of replay value and cool tricks, including multiple versions of levels and a great set of upgrades (10 in all).  The only drawbacks are some somewhat uninteresting mavericks and that the ability to play as Zero is almost pointless in the gameplay.  It's still cool though.  ;)<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Story</div>

<div class=itemtext>Reploid scientist Dr. Doppler has discovered the cause of the mavericks' rebellion.  The maverick cmuptrer virus, which Dr. Doppler eradicates with an antivirus.  He founds a utopia, Dopplertown, where reploids live in peace and prosperity.  However, Dr. Doppler goes maverick himself, and converts the reploids of Dopplertown too.

<p><a href=x3spoilers.html target=_blank>SPOILERS</a><br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Unique Features</div>

<div class=itemtext>Like X2, X3 uses the C4 chip and has mini-bosses.  The C4 chip is used a bit less in this one, or at least not used as noticably, although this game uses it for one of MM's attacks, the charged-up spin blade.  The mini-boss feature in X3 is spectacular because the way you play the mini-bosses actually decides what levels you play in Doppler's fortress.  One of them is Vile, who has his own hidden mini-level with entrances in several of the maverick levels, and the other 2 are Bit and Byte, who have boss rooms in each maverick level.  Vile's mini-level is very cool, but unfortunately, Bit and Byte aren't as interesting as the X-Hunters, and the fact that their boss rooms aren't hidden is just annoying.  Defeat them normally and you'll fight them again in Dr. Doppler's fortress, or use their vulnerability weapons and you'll get different bosses, and in Vile's case, a very different version of the 2nd fortress stage.

<p>This is the first MM action game where you can play as multiple characters.  However, you can only play as Zero once per level, and he can't enter boss rooms (which makes the mandatory boss rooms even more annoying).  He's about as powerful as a half-upgraded X, though his Beam Sabre is REALLY nice and extremely powerful.

<p>The previous X games had 5 upgrades - 4 regular upgrades and 1 secret upgrade.  X3 doubles that number.  Besides the Helmet, X-Buster, Dash, and Armor upgrades, you can also get special chips that extend each of these upgrades even further.  However, you can only use 1, which is really cool for replay value.  The best of the 4 is probably the double-dash.  The secret upgrades are Zero's Beam Sabre (which is even more useful with X because his version has range), and a secret gold armor upgrade that gives you all 4 of the upgrade chips at once.  With both the gold armor and Beam Sabre, Sigma is about as tough as Flame Mammoth.  :P  But it's still a ton of fun to breeze through the levels and try to defeat bosses in the coolest way possible.  :P<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Passwords</div>

<div class=itemtext><br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

